Ahead of the Saturday gubernatorial election, one of the spokespersons for Atiku, Okowa Presidential Campaign Council, Senator Dino Melaye, has attacked the All Progressives Congress, APC, governorship candidate in Delta State, Ovie Omo-Agege, describing him as a ‘mace thief.’ Melaye also called Omo-Agege, a Deputy Senate President, ‘nepotism pro max’. His statement is contained in a post via his Twitter handle on Tuesday. The former lawmaker accused Omo-Agege of cornering all the allocated federal projects to his home town, Orogun. According to Melaye, the five projects were: Defence Space Academy, Law School, Jamb CBT center, Oil and Gas Industrial Park and Independent Power Plant. He wrote, “Don’t vote a mace thief.”